quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,103,"And when they had both submitted{1} and he put him down upon his forehead,",footnotes:1:To the command of Allāh.
  37,104,"We called to him, "
  37,105,"You have fulfilled the vision."
  38,82,"[Iblees] said, "
  38,83,"Except, among them, Your chosen servants."
  38,84,"[Allāh] said, "
  39,67,"They have not appraised Allāh with true appraisal,{1} while the earth entirely will be [within] His grip{2} on the Day of Resurrection, and the heavens will be folded in His right hand.{3} Exalted is He and high above what they associate with Him.",footnotes:1:[i.e., appreciation of His attributes.],footnotes:2:[Literally, \"no more than a handful of His.\"],footnotes:3:[See footnote to 2:19.]
  39,68,"And the Horn will be blown, and whoever is in the heavens and whoever is on the earth will fall dead except whom Allāh wills. Then it will be blown again, and at once they will be standing, looking on."
  39,69,"And the earth will shine with the light of its Lord, and the record [of deeds] will be placed, and the prophets and the witnesses will be brought, and it will be judged between them in truth, and they will not be wronged."
  40,46,"The Fire; they are exposed to it morning and evening.{1} And the Day the Hour appears [it will be said], ",footnotes:1:From the time of their death until the Day of Resurrection, when they will be driven into it.
  40,47,"And [mention] when they will argue within the Fire, and the weak will say to those who had been arrogant, "
  40,48,"Those who had been arrogant will say, "
  41,25,"And We appointed for them companions{1} who made attractive to them what was before them and what was behind them [of sin], and the word [i.e., decree] has come into effect upon them among nations which had passed on before them of jinn and men. Indeed, they [all] were losers.",footnotes:1:In this world among the evil jinn and men.
  41,26,"And those who disbelieve say, ",footnotes:1:Other meanings include "speak improperly" and/or "make a clamor."  The purpose of this was to prevent the hearing or understanding of the Qur’ān.
  41,27,"But We will surely cause those who disbelieve to taste a severe punishment, and We will surely recompense them for the worst of what they had been doing."
  42,10,"And in anything over which you disagree - its ruling is [to be referred] to Allāh. [Say], ",footnotes:1:In remembrance and repentance.
  42,11,"[He is] Creator of the heavens and the earth. He has made for you from yourselves, mates, and among the cattle, mates; He multiplies you thereby. There is nothing like unto Him,{1} and He is the Hearing, the Seeing.{2}",footnotes:1:[There is no similarity whatsoever between the Creator and His creation in essence, in attributes or in deed.],footnotes:2:[See footnotes to 17:1.]
  42,12,"To Him belong the keys of the heavens and the earth. He extends provision for whom He wills and restricts [it]. Indeed He is, of all things, Knowing."
